{"lemma": "كَلْبٌ", "slug": "كَلْبٌ", "root": "ك.ل.ب", "root_slug": "ك-ل-ب", "root_link": "/words/roots/ك-ل-ب", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "كَلْب", "root": "كلب", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 5}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 4, "pos_tags": ["adj", "noun", "verb"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 11}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n37142"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%83%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "dog", "fa": "سگ", "ur": "کتا", "tr": "köpek", "id": "anjing", "bn": "কুকুর", "es": "perro", "fr": "chien", "de": "Hund", "ru": "собака", "zh": "狗"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "dog"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to be seized by hydrophobia, to become rabid"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to become mad, to become crazy"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to covet greedily"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "verbal noun of كَلِبَ (kaliba) (form I)", "tags": ["form-of", "noun-from-verb"]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "rabies, hydrophobia", "examples": [{"text": "دَاء الْكَلَب", "english": "rabies, hydrophobia"}]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "burning thirst"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "greed"}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "rabid, affected with rabies"}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "mad"}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "greedy"}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "From Proto-Semitic *kalb-. Cognate with Akkadian 𒌨𒂠 (kalbum) and Biblical Hebrew כֶּלֶב (kɛ́lɛḇ).\n\nLikely denominal to كَلَب (kalab, “rabies”) or directly to كَلْب (kalb, “dog”).\n\nLikely derived from كَلْب (kalb, “dog”)."}, "ipa": ["/kalb/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n37142", "headword_ar": "كَلْبٌ", "root": "klb", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "a word of well-known signification, [The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "dog:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] (S:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "any wounding animal of prey:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(L, K, &c.:) but whether birds [of prey] are comprised in this term is a point that requires consideration: (Esh-Shiháb El-Khafájee:) and especially applied to the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "barking animal"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "dog"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (K:) or rather, this is its proper signification; and it admits no other: (MF:) sometimes used as an epithet; as in the ex."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_imoraA^apN kalobapN", "text_ar": "اـِمْرَاَةٌ كَلْبَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A woman like a bitch; a woman who is a bitch"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (S:) pl. [of pauc.]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^akolubN", "text_ar": "اَكْلُبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and (of mult., TA,)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kilaAbN", "text_ar": "كِلَابٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kaliybN", "text_ar": "كَلِيبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which is a rare [form of] pl., like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EabiydN", "text_ar": "عَبِيدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EabodN", "text_ar": "عَبْدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", [or rather a quasi-pl. n.,] (S,) and (pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^akolubN", "text_ar": "اَكْلُبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", S,)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^akaAlibu", "text_ar": "اَكَالِبُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K) and (pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kilaAbN", "text_ar": "كِلَابٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", TA,)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kilaAbaAtN", "text_ar": "كِلَابَاتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K) and (also pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kilaAbN", "text_ar": "كِلَابٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^akaAliybu", "text_ar": "اَكَالِيبُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (Msb:)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kilaAbN", "text_ar": "كِلَابٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is also used as a pl. of pauc.;"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "valaAvapu kilaAbK", "text_ar": "ثَلَاثَةُ كِلَابٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "being said for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "vlAvpN mina AlkilaAbi", "text_ar": "ثلاثةٌ مِنَ الكِلَابِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "klAb", "text_ar": "كلاب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "being used in this case for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^akolubK", "text_ar": "اَكْلُبٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (Sb:)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kaliybN", "text_ar": "كَلِيبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kaAlibN", "text_ar": "كَالِبٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signify"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a pack,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "collected number, of dogs:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K:) [both are quasi-pl. ns. in my opinion, though the former is called a pl. in the S:] accord. to some, the former, if masc., is a quasipl. n. ; and if fem., a pl.: (MF:) the latter is like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jaAmilN", "text_ar": "جَامِلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baAqirN", "text_ar": "بَاقِرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[which are both quasi-pl. ns.]. (L.) The pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kalobapN", "text_ar": "كَلْبَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[the fem.] is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kilaAbN", "text_ar": "كِلَابٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kalabaAtN", "text_ar": "كَلَبَاتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Msb.) ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fulaAnN biwaAdiY Alkalobi", "text_ar": "فُلَانٌ بِوَادِى الكَلْبِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Such a one is in the valley of the dog:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] said of one whom no one cares for, and who has no place of abode or resort, but is like a dog, which one sees ever going forth into the desert. ―         -b3-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kaf~a Eanohu kilaAbahu", "text_ar": "كَفَّ عَنْهُ كِلَابَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He left reviling him, and injuring"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "annoying him:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[lit., restrained from him his dogs]. (A.) See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kalabN", "text_ar": "كَلَبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". ―         -b4-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlkilaAbu ElY Albaqar i", "text_ar": "الكِلَابُ على البَقَر ِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, K,) the first word being in the nom. case as an inchoative, (TA,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlkilaAba", "text_ar": "الكِلَابَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, K,) put in the acc. case as governed by a verb understood, (TA,) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlkiraAbu", "text_ar": "الكِرَابُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlkiraAba", "text_ar": "الكِرَابَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (Kh, S, art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "krb", "text_ar": "كرب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", K;) of which readings, that of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlklAb", "text_ar": "الكلاب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is the one generally adopted; (TA;) or they are two distinct proverbs, each having its proper meaning; (Meyd;) the former signifying, [if we read"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlkilaAba", "text_ar": "الكِلَابَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Send the dogs against the wild oxen:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e., leave a man and his art: (S, K:) [but accord. to MF, this is the meaning if we read"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "krAb", "text_ar": "كراب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; but if we read"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "klAb", "text_ar": "كلاب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", the signification is, as explained above, “ Send the dogs &c., ” and the proverb is applied on the occasion of instigating one set of people against another set, without caring for what may happen to them:] or it alludes to a man's having little care or solicitude for the state, or case, or affair, of his companion. (A 'Obeyd.) If we read"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlklAbu", "text_ar": "الكلابُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", the meaning is"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The dogs are upon,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "against, the wild oxen:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and in like manner, if we read"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlkrAbu", "text_ar": "الكرابُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", the meaning is “ The turning over of the soil is the work of the oxen: ” if"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlkrAba", "text_ar": "الكرابَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", “ Leave the turning over of the soil to the oxen. ” (MF, from expositions of the Fs.) ―         -b5-  ["}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kalobN", "text_ar": "كَلْبٌ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kalibN", "text_ar": "كَلِبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "seems also to signify"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A fierce,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "furious, dog."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "See"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaqanobaApN", "text_ar": "عَقَنْبَاةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".] ―         -b6-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kalobu Albar~i", "text_ar": "كَلْبُ البَرِّ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The dog of the desert;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the wolf."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "*iy^ob", "text_ar": "ذِيْب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) ―         -b7-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kalobN", "text_ar": "كَلْبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is also especially applied to"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A lion."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K, TA.) ―         -b8-  The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "first increase of water in a valley."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Nh, K.) ―         -b9-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A piece of iron at the head of the"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 2626}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "pivot,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "axis, of a mill."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K.) ―         -b10-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A piece of wood by which a wall is propped,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "supported."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K.) ―         -b11-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A certain fish"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in the form of a dog."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ["}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kalobu AlbaHori", "text_ar": "كَلْبُ البَحْرِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alkalobu AlbaHoriY~u", "text_ar": "الكَلْبُ البَحْرِىُّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "are appellations now applied to"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The shark."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]       -A2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kalobN", "text_ar": "كَلْبٌ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A strap,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "thong, cut from an untanned skin,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mukal~abN", "text_ar": "مُكَلَّبٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is A man"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "bound with a"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kalob", "text_ar": "كَلْب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", i. e., with a"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "strap,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "thong, cut from an untanned skin."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.)       -A3-  The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text