kind": "text", "text": "(or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a red"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aHomar", "text_ar": "اَحْمَر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[probably a mistake for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A=xar", "text_ar": "ا=خَر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "another"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "strap, &c.,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "which is put between the two edges of a skin"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "when it is sewed."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S.)       -A6-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kalobu Alfarasi", "text_ar": "كَلْبُ الفَرَسِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The line,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "streak, that is in the middle of the horse's back."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K.) ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_isotawaY", "text_ar": "اـِسْتَوَى"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EalaY kalobi farasihi", "text_ar": "عَلَى كَلْبِ فَرَسِهِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He sat firmly upon the line,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "streak, in the middle of his horse's back."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S.) ―         -b3-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kalobN", "text_ar": "كَلْبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kal~aAbN", "text_ar": "كَلَّابٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "An iron at the edge of a camel's saddle of the kind called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "raHol", "text_ar": "رَحْل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (K:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a bent,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "crooked,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "hooked, iron, by which the traveller hangs, from the saddle"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rHl", "text_ar": "رحل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "),"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "his travelling-provisions"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and his"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^adaAwiY", "text_ar": "اَدَاوِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fahodN", "text_ar": "فَهْدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". ―         -b4-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kalobN", "text_ar": "كَلْبٌ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Anything with which a thing is made firm,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "fast,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "is bound:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "syn."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kul~umaA wuv~iqa bihi $aYo'N", "text_ar": "كُلُّمَا وُثِّقَ بِهِ شَىْءٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (as in some copies of the K,) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^uwviqa", "text_ar": "اُوثِقَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(as in others): so called because it holds fast a thing like a dog. (TA.) ―         -b5-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kalobN", "text_ar": "كَلْبٌ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "i. q."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$aEiyrapN", "text_ar": "شَعِيرَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[app. meaning the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$Eyrp", "text_ar": "شعيرة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of the handle of a knife &c.]. (S.) ―         -b6-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lisaAnu Alkalobi", "text_ar": "لِسَانُ الكَلْبِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A certain plant;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K;) ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "cynoglossum,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "dog's tongue"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. ―         -b7-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kaf~u Alkalobi", "text_ar": "كَفُّ الكَلْبِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A certain spreading herb,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "which grows in the plain low tracts of Nejd; thus called when it has dried, in which case it is likened to the paw of a dog; but while it continues green, it is called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kft", "text_ar": "كفت"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) ―         -b8-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^um~u kalobK", "text_ar": "اُمُّ كَلْبٍ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A certain small thorny tree,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "which grows in rugged ground, and upon the mountains, having yellow leaves, and rough; when it is put in motion, it diffuses a most fetid and foul smell:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "so called because of its thorns, or because it stinks like a dog when rain falls upon him. (TA.)       -A7-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^um~u kalobapa", "text_ar": "اُمُّ كَلْبَةَ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Fever."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K.) So called because it keeps to a man with much tenacity, like a dog. (TA.) ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laqiytu minohu A@sota Alkalobapi", "text_ar": "لَقِيتُ مِنْهُ ا@سْتَ الكَلْبَةِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", a prov.: see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AisotN", "text_ar": "اِسْتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sth", "text_ar": "سته"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".       -A8-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alkalobu AlA^akobaru", "text_ar": "الكَلْبُ الاَكْبَرُ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The constellation of Canis Major:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "its principal star, Sirius."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(El-Kazweenee &c.) ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alkalobu AlA^aSogaru", "text_ar": "الكَلْبُ الاَصْغَرُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", also called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alklb Almutaqad~imu", "text_ar": "الكلب المُتَقَدِّمُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The constellation of Canis Minor:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "its principal star, Procyon."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(El-Kazweenee &c.) ―         -b3-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alkalobu", "text_ar": "الكَلْبُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kalobu Alr~aAEiY", "text_ar": "كَلْبُ الرَّاعِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A certain star, over against"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ald~alowu", "text_ar": "الدَّلْوُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(q. v.), ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "which is"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "below; in the path of which is a red star, called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alr~aAEiY", "text_ar": "الرَّاعِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (TA:)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "klb", "text_ar": "كلب"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlrAEY", "text_ar": "الراعى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is a name given to"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a star between the feet,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "legs, of Cepheus;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlrEY", "text_ar": "الرعى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", to that which is upon his left foot, or leg; (El-Kazweenee;) [app., from their longitudes, the same two stars to which the above quotation from the TA relates: but the same two names are also given to two other stars.] ―         -b4-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "klb AlrEY", "text_ar": "كلب الرعى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is [likewise] a name given to The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "star which is on,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in, the head of Hercules;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlHAwY", "text_ar": "الحاوى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", an evident mistake in my MS. of El-Kazweenee, I read"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AljaAviY", "text_ar": "الجَاثِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ";] that in the head of Ophiuchus ("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlHaw~aA'u", "text_ar": "الحَوَّاءُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ") being called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlrAEY", "text_ar": "الراعى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (El-Kazweenee.) ―         -b5-  ["}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlkalobaAni", "text_ar": "الكَلْبَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", accord. to Freytag,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A name of the two stars        \n      υ and        \n      κ which belong to Taurus:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "but accord. to my MS. of El-Kazweenee, the two stars that are near together on the ears of Taurus are called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlkuloyataAni", "text_ar": "الكُلْيَتَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".] ―         -b6-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kilaAbu Al$~itaA'i", "text_ar": "كِلَابُ الشِّتَاءِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The stars,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "asterisms, of the beginning of winter; namely,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Al*~iraAEu", "text_ar": "الذِّرَاعُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alm~avorapu", "text_ar": "المَّثْرَةُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlT~arofu", "text_ar": "الطَّرْفُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aljabohapu", "text_ar": "الجَبْهَةُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the 7th, 8th, 9th, and 10th, of the Mansions of the Moon:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "so called because they set aurorally in the winter: the first so set, about the period of the commencement of the era of the Flight, in central Arabia, on the 3rd of January: see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "manaAzilu Alqamari", "text_ar": "مَنَازِلُ القَمَرِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "nzl", "text_ar": "نزل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["S", "K", "MF", "Msb", "Sb", "TA", "L"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}